						               													<description>Slide and meld fragments into words in this lasercut word game. The game components include 144 letter, bigram and trigram tiles, each with a point value and a gameboard with angular stands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setup: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Assemble the board with the stands&amp;#10;     Shuffle and scatter the tiles face down in a random pile&amp;#10;     Grab 30 tiles and randomly stack face up within the slots&amp;#10;         2 players:    30 tiles&amp;#10;         3 players:    50 tiles&amp;#10;         4 players:    70 tiles&amp;#10;         5+ players:    90 tiles&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;     Reserve a pile of face down tiles in a draw pile as per the number of players:&amp;#10;     Set the remaining tiles aside and out of sight.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Play: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Pull one tile from the bottom of any column, letting the tiles in the column slide down.&amp;#10;     Add a tile from the draw pile face up to the top of same column, except when there is only one tile left which is placed face down as the game-ending mystery tile.&amp;#10;     Attempt to make a word from two or more of your tiles.&amp;#10;     When made, place your word in a separate collection pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ending the Game: The game ends when someone pulls the face down mystery tile. That player gets to use that tile to form a word, if possible. At this point the game ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
